00:00:00,634 --> 00:00:03,264
Mom, you found my jacket.

2
00:00:03,264 --> 00:00:05,855
You're the best mom in
the whole wide world.

3
00:00:06,439 --> 00:00:10,417
Go, Scat, get out of here.
You're gonna be late.

4
00:00:10,417 --> 00:00:11,751
Where's dad?

5
00:00:11,751 --> 00:00:13,858
Ed, Stevie's going now!

6
00:00:13,858 --> 00:00:15,712
Hold on a minute!
Don't go!

7
00:00:15,712 --> 00:00:18,410
Can anyone in this house
just talk at a normal level?

8
00:00:18,410 --> 00:00:20,085
Say "cheese."

9
00:00:21,793 --> 00:00:23,824
Doesn't he look handsome, Ed?

10
00:00:23,824 --> 00:00:26,083
Mom, don't get all weepy. Jeez.

11
00:00:26,083 --> 00:00:29,549
Wear your seatbelt tonight.
It's pouring cats and dogs out there.

12
00:00:29,549 --> 00:00:32,873
Better get out of here before mom decides 
she's going to the prom with you.

13
00:00:32,873 --> 00:00:35,739
Okay. Parental units, 
I'm out of here.

14
00:00:36,099 --> 00:00:38,256
Don't forget your keys.

15
00:00:42,180 --> 00:00:43,981
The Caddy?

16
00:00:45,928 --> 00:00:47,208
Are you serious, dad?

17
00:00:47,208 --> 00:00:50,310
Could be making the biggest
mistake of my life.

18
00:00:51,977 --> 00:00:54,584
- Thanks, dad.
- Have a great time, son.

19
00:00:54,584 --> 00:00:56,230
Be careful.

20
00:01:01,177 --> 00:01:02,641
Bye.

21
00:01:03,030 --> 00:01:04,844
Bye.

22
00:02:44,899 --> 00:02:46,828
Are you a detective?

23
00:02:46,828 --> 00:02:48,270
Yeah.

24
00:02:48,711 --> 00:02:50,675
Can I help you?

25
00:02:51,278 --> 00:02:54,488
I have information on a murder.

26
00:02:54,488 --> 00:02:56,760
The boy who died.

27
00:02:58,957 --> 00:03:02,288
His name was Steve Jablonski.

28
00:03:02,288 --> 00:03:03,903
Jablonski.

29
00:03:04,654 --> 00:03:06,976
Sounds familiar.

30
00:03:06,976 --> 00:03:11,322
He was buried alive 26 years ago.

31
00:03:12,473 --> 00:03:14,493
Right.

32
00:03:14,493 --> 00:03:15,807
That was horrible.

33
